Read the full instructions for a skill by name.

Workers see a listing of available skills (name + description) in the `<available_skills>` section of their system prompt. That listing is a summary. Call this tool to load the full skill body before starting any task that matches one of those skills.

You may call this tool multiple times if a task spans more than one skill.

## Parameters

- `name` — the skill name, exactly as it appears in `<available_skills>`. Case-sensitive.

## When to call

- Before starting work on a task whose description matches a listed skill.
- When the user references a skill by name.
- When another tool's output points at a skill (e.g. `skills_search`).

## Errors

Returns an error if the requested name is not in the runtime skill registry. The error message lists no alternatives; re-check `<available_skills>` in your system prompt for the exact name.
